title: calendario_
content:
#!/usr/bin/env python3
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
Crea un calendario para el año especificado y 
lo imprime a "calendario.pdf"
@author: JP
"""

from fpdf import FPDF
import calendar


class PDF(FPDF):
    def header(self):
        self.set_font("Courier", "B", 12)
        self.cell(0, 10, "Calendario", 0, 1, "C")
        self.ln(5)

    def footer(self):
        self.set_y(-15)
        self.set_font("Courier", "I", 8)
        self.cell(0, 10, f"Página {self.page_no()}", 0, 0, "C")


def generar_calendario(anio):
    # Crear un objeto PDF
    pdf = PDF()
    pdf.alias_nb_pages()
    pdf.add_page()

    # Generar el calendario para el año especificado en español
    locale = calendar.LocaleTextCalendar(locale="es_ES.utf8")
    calendario = locale.formatyear(anio, 2, 1, 1, 3)

    # Agregar el calendario al PDF con margen izquierdo ampliado
    pdf.set_font("Courier", "", 10)
    pdf.set_left_margin(40)  # Ajustar el margen izquierdo a 40 unidades
    pdf.multi_cell(0, 5, calendario)

    # Guardar el archivo PDF
    pdf.output("calendario.pdf")


# Obtener el año del usuario
anio = int(input("Ingrese el año: "))

# Generar el calendario y guardarlo en PDF
generar_calendario(anio)
print("Calendario generado y guardado en calendario.pdf")

title: Changelog 02/03/2025
content:
General Changes
+ Fixed holstering penalties not properly being set
New change to weapon stats being attributed cause this issue, which should be resolved now resorting these downsides.

Equalizer
+ Particle effect replaced such that it doesn't go through walls
Prior particle was a bit too distracting and overly visible, this one ought to be better hidden while still being noticeable.

Scorch Shot
+ Flare no longer bounces off of buildings
Update to better allow flare to bounce as applied to liberally, now should just instantly explode against buildings.

Ullapool Caber
+ Fixed charge inconsistently recharging after killing enemies
Charge was instantly refilling inconsistently at times, now should properly start at 0% and potentially more when a killed enemy's ammo is collected.

Natascha
+ Increased health-on-hit to max out at 9 per hit (was 8 per hit)
Reverting fire rate had cut the healing too much, so this slight buff should bring it closer to what its rate once was.

Bazaar Bargain
~ Press SPECIAL ATTACK to use up 1 Head while charging
+ Using the Head doubles your charge damage bonus
- Gain stronger tracer on this shot
- Bonus damage is lost on unscoping
While the weapon was in a more balanced state, it didn't appear to provide enough reward for the sake of snowballing. With this change we are allowing Heads to be used as a resource to temporarily negate the charge damage penalty, allowing you to take advantage of the charge bonus with the full damage at the cost of potentially setting your next charge back - on top of committing to hardscoping.

The Bushwacka
+ Added: On hit, marks enemy for death for 2 seconds 
- Added -25% damage penalty
- This weapon deploys 50% slower
The weapon had been requested to be changed for quite some time, due to it's excessively linear design and forced synergy on Sniper's kit. This current version takes it in the direction of giving it some means of applying the mini-crits it requires to self-combo, at the cost of being made weaker when comboing with other forms of minicrits.
